N2  - Abstract This paper develops a quality-adjusted measure of marginal housing rents using a monthly statistic of landlord net rental income. The marginal rent index (MRI) exhibits deflation during recessions and leads the official rent index by 7 months. The modified inflation rate based on MRI suggests that the annual official inflation rate was overestimated by 1.7?4.1% during the Great Recession but underestimated by 0.3?0.7% during the subsequent expansionary period.
